A slightly more difficult challenge, involving an incomplete password script. Requirements: Common sense.

Network Security Sam set up a password protection script. He made it load the real password from an unencrypted text file and compare it to the password the user enters. **However, he neglected to upload the password file...**

similar to previous challenge the page provided a password input field and a submit button

as you can see sam didn't upload the password file and that's again what makes this challenge easy but uses common sense

just press "Submit" without giving any password because since there is no password file to check the input password with...

yeah you get it 

